    "body": "With https://github.com/KMiri-rs/KMiri/issues/90 fixed, now we have the ub report\n\n```rust\nTerminate ThreadId(1). Live thread count: 1 (Thread: [\"main\"])\nerror: Undefined Behavior: constructing invalid value of type !: encountered a value of the never type `!`\n   --> /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/boot/mod.rs:142:14\n    |\n142 |     unsafe { __ostd_main() };\n    |              ^^^^^^^^^^^^^ Undefined Behavior occurred here\n    |\n    = help: this indicates a bug in the program: it performed an invalid operation, and caused Undefined Behavior\n    = help: see https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/reference/behavior-considered-undefined.html for further information\n    = note: this is on thread `main`\n    = note: stack backtrace:\n            0: ostd::boot::start_kernel\n                at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/boot/mod.rs:142:14: 142:27\n            1: ostd::arch::boot::miri_boot\n                at /home/zjp/KMiri/asterinas/ostd/src/arch/miri/boot/mod.rs:73:14: 73:28\n            2: miri_start\n                at src/main.rs:18:5: 18:34\n```\n\n`__ostd_main` is [defined](https://github.com/KMiri-rs/asterinas/blob/2bf3f4386a688082042f5247103fad0e3539feda/ostd/src/boot/mod.rs#L133-L142) as an external function returning the never type.\n\nFor miri's `__ostd_main` [implementaion](https://github.com/KMiri-rs/asterinas/blob/2bf3f4386a688082042f5247103fad0e3539feda/ostd/libs/ostd-macros/src/lib.rs#L142-L163), the main thread continues due to no task, and the function successfully returns.\n\nA fix is to call `miri_terminate_current_thread` on the main thread, and tell kmiri the program exits successfully.\n\n\n",
